<br>
From what I understand, two different views:<br>
1) Satan exists and his is powerful and if worshipped will reward his devotees.<br>
2) Satan doesn't exists - only a symbol of fleshly human desires and appetites.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.churchofsatan.com/home.html" target="top">The Church of Satan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, (as opposed to the link given in another thread) founded by Anton Lavey who made the following statement in the satanic bible -<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Satan represents indulgence instead of abstinence.  Satan represents vital existence instead of spiritual pipe dreams.  Satan represent vengeance instead of turning the other cheek.  Satan represents all the so-called sins, as that all lead to physical, mental, or emotional gratification...&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Umm...no thanks.<br>
<br>
The Temple of Set (Founded by Dr. Michael Aquino) I believe was an offspring of Lavey's church.  He claimed to have had a revelation from satan informing him to begin afresh with an organization that would worship the true powers of darkness.  <br>
<br>
Hmmm...communication with satan....again, no thanks.<br>
<br>
Whether traditional, non-traditional, public, dabblers, or individuals on their own...Any way I look at it, I'm not seeing a whole lot that I could possibly agree with.<br>
<br>
I also remember DBC knowing something about this, maybe he can shed a little more light?<br>
<br>
Candy<br>
