<br>
I'm not a huge fan of Satanism myself because:<br>
1. If you believe in Satan in a godlike way--whether he's equal to god or you think he's good/evil aside, you're a theist and I am an atheist. There is no more reason to believe in Satan than god, Jesus, spirits, fairies...In this way, Satanists are JUST LIKE xians, Jews, Muslims etc. they just worship a different god--and not necessarily a less violent one. He is certainly invoked in the name of murder, rape, pillaging and war in general FAR less often than Jehovah. <br>
<br>
2. If he's not a god, then choosing to go by the name causes undue confusion and false assumptions, particularly from xians who can be a fairly rabid bunch already against those who don't share their beliefs. Why burden yourself with a xian-based title for a belief system? I guess I can sort of see how they are trying to portray themselves as following the opposite of some of what's in the bible....but again, using Satan..oh well..<br>
<br>
3. While most of the self-gratifying things are harmless (even those that advocate revenge do so only toward adults who have caused you harm--no children or animals which already places them above xians), the absence of a measure for utilitarianism doesn't sit with me. I don't care about praying for better sex---how can THAT be wrong<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , but there is great value in deferred gratification, even if the goal is a greater gratification in the end (saving for retirement, saving for a better toy/car/house so you are happier in long run, eating right to feel better later). <br>
<br>
I am not as familiar with Satanists as DBC, but find them far less threatening than xians and often times indistinguishable in lifestyle. It is simply not a religion that causes people to roam around hurting others, especially when compared to xianity. A mite too hedonistic for my taste? Sure, but this doesn't make it immoral...<br>
<br>
