<br>
<br>
Does the Devil really exist? If so, what does he look like?<br>
<br>
Some Satanists view the Devil as the first individual - the first being to acquire consciousness and self-awareness. This lends itself to free will and is the true meaning behind Lucifer's &quot;fall from grace.&quot; We are all inheritors of that gift, so if you are asking me what the devil looks like, I would simply tell you to go look in a mirror.<br>
<br>
<br>
Their ideas about the relationship between man and the duality of god/devil is so interesting.  I obviously disagree, as I don't believe in either a god or devil figure, and I find their devotion to self-service off-putting--but it's a fascinating pov nonetheless.<br>
<br>
-Simone  <br>
