He detailed an account written by &quot;mortal prophets&quot; during Lucifer's fall from grace.  It states that the angels that helped God in creation loved their creation as they loved God, and were commanded to do so.  They were also commanded to stay hidden from the creation they labored over and loved so deeply.  Eventually, the angels fell to bickering over which commandment was more important; to love creation equal to God, or to hide themselves from the eyes of creation.  This dispute came to a head when Lucifer, the first Morningstar, decided to *takes a call* lead those angels that felt it unfair to hide themselves from creation in open revolt against the will of God.<br>
