Thought that was kind of an interesting spin on Lucifer.  From the &quot;evil conniving Prince of Darkness&quot; in the Christian standpoint, to a bit of a martyr who loved creation too much.  Hmm... <p>You know what they say...  rub the Tummy and you'll have good luck all day...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> M2</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#3333ff>(4/15/03 4:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   LDS view on him</span><hr size=1> The LDS view isnt a far stretch from that last idea.  We beleive were all a big family Heavenly Father, Heavenly Mother and all of us little spirit kids.  As we grew and developed and matured, the time came when the only way we could progress any further was to come to an earth and gain a body.<br>
<br>
Two plans arose.  The first was Heavenly Fathers plan. That a world would be created and we could come down here and be given free agency. The right to choose to follow God and all the eternal laws or not.  But because he knew we would make mistakes, there would be a need for a savior to pay for our sins so that we could overcome evil and return to our Heavenly Family.  Jesus Christ, the eldest son of our Father, volunteered to be the Savior.<br>
<br>
Second plan, arose when Satan didnt like the first plan.  his alternative was to force us to all behave and not have free-will and because all of us would return, he wanted to have all of Gods glory.  That plan was rejected, because the whole purpose of earth was to gain wisdom and understanding from our mistakes.  Satan was mad.  This is the war in heaven spoken about in revelations.  So he did all he could to convince the rest of us to follow him.  One third of HF's children did and they were cast out.  Every one else (those of us born on the earth) chose HF plan.<br>
<br>
Christ and other valiant spirits did create the earth under the direction of HF and Satan and his followers were allowed to come here to tempt us.  So Satan is still peeved that he will never have a body.  His main goal (still) is to get us to use our agency to follow him in rebellion against God.  So in a way the satanist are right in that he was the first to use his agency to rebel against God. But to me that isnt a good thing.<br>
<br>
